About FedEx Supply Chain
FedEx Supply Chain, a subsidiary of FedEx Corp. (NYSE: FDX), is a leader in the third-party logistics industry offering a diverse service portfolio that enables commerce for businesses. With a proven track record of innovation and operational excellence, FedEx Supply Chain takes a consultative approach to optimize logistics processes, implement innovative technology and drive continuous improvement. By leveraging best practices and the world-renowned FedEx network, FedEx Supply Chain delivers leading solutions that provide flexibility, enable scalability and improve cost-effectiveness for customers. Through more than 11,000 employees, 130 operations and 35 million square feet of warehouse space, FedEx Supply Chain manages nearly 150 million packages and processes 358 million returns each year. For more information, go to supplychain.fedex.com.

Title: User Experience Designer - Sr User Experience Designer
Job_Description:
At FedEx Ground, we believe in customer-driven design solutions. Learning from our customers helps build viable, feasible, and desirable solutions to problems and grow through innovation. The User Experience Designer is the lead in designing engaging and effective user experiences for our product development, collaborating with the Product Group and Product Developers to discover, design, engineer and deliver new solutions through the entire product development lifecycle. User experience and design is an integrated part of the full end-to-end product development process, from strategy, and workflow planning, to user experience design, and testing sign off. Understand user process and design the interface based on their process. Will partner with front end developers and Product Owners for engineering and standardization We are looking for designers who are passionate about understanding people, committed to lifelong learning, are creative, and driven by the love of what they do.

Provide expert leadership at the enterprise level related to vast quantities of data (including disparate data), enterprise analytics, statistical modeling, and initiatives. Leads staff in advanced in descriptive, diagnostic, predictive, prescriptive and ensemble modeling, advanced statistical techniques, use of database tools and/or other approaches in quantitative analysis of complex business situations. Creates and implements solutions from initial concept to fully tested production and communicates results to a broad range of audiences. Expert use of current and emerging technologies to evaluate trends and develop actionable insights and recommendations to managements, via understanding of the business model and the information available for analysis. Expert use of all data types, statistical and quantitative analysis, explanatory and high- complexity predictive modeling and fact-based management to drive decision making. Mentors fewer senior staff. Leads cross functional projects and programs. Routinely works on multiple highly complex assignments concurrently.

Minimum Qualifications:
Master's degree or equivalent in a quantitative discipline required. seven (7) Year work experience in measurement and analysis, quantitative business problem solving, solutions implementation, operations analysis, marketing analysis, simulation development and/or predictive analytics. Demonstrated superior analytical skills with diverse analytics, data types and statistical software and applications. Outstanding interpersonal skills, written, and oral communication skill. Proven leadership skills.

Master’s degree in or equivalent in a quantitative discipline required plus 7 years of experience in the job offered or 7 years of experience in measurement and analysis, quantitative business problem solving, solutions implementation, operations analysis, marketing analysis, simulation development and/or predictive analytics. Demonstrated superior analytical skills with diverse analytics, data types and statistical software and applications. Outstanding interpersonal skills, written, and oral communication skill. Proven leadership skills. The employer will alternatively accept a Bachelor’s in a quantitative discipline and 9 years of experience in measurement and analysis, quantitative business problem solving, solutions implementation, operations analysis, marketing analysis, simulation development and/or predictive analytics. Demonstrated superior analytical skills with diverse analytics, data types and statistical software and applications. Outstanding interpersonal skills, written, and oral communication skill. The Engineering and Financial Analysis (EFA) group within the Analytical Support Department (ASD) leads the development of strategic business cases for the Latin America and Caribbean division, including but not limited to: - System form changes - Corporate development projects - Strategic growth and/or profit improvement initiatives The ideal candidate can articulate the strategic intent and operational/commercial/financial impacts of a strategic initiative in a concise manner.
